Hi Adriene, just wanted to pop in to say how grateful I am for your online classes. I did the first 20 days without skipping a beat - although I wasn't sure if I could do so at the beginning. After all, I am a borderline kyphotic scoliotic who tried every play in the book (pilates, swimming, etc.) to improve my posture with no sustained results. I find this 30 days idea so compelling, because it is different everyday and you are an excellent instructor. You are so good at verbal cueing that I don't even have to look at the screen anymore, even though my Yoga experience is very limited. I am seeing the results since day 1, and my posture seems to "stay" better even after a long day's work. THANK YOU from the bottom of my heart. 
p.s. I literally cried from joy when I saw that there are several other 30 day challenges on your channel! I can't wait to do everything on this channel :) and will probably sign up to your website, too. Namaste!

Day 20: Yoga with Adriene - Heart Practice. So I didn't leave myself enough time to get in practice before hockey tonight. I wasnt expecting to do get to practice today. However I went and played hockey and didn't see a whole lot of shots. I came home and felt rather unfulfilled, so I rolled out my mat and got to my practice. This was a wonderful session with lots of very deep breathing and breathing rhythms. This session isn't all that physically intensive, however it is nice as a form of meditation. I loved the breathing and the arm vinyasas. I really fell into the ending vinyasas in our kneeling pose. I didnt want them to stop. However I followed through along with Adriene and came to shavasana. I feel much much better afterwards. Thanks for a wonderful session Adriene! Namaste.

I have herniated disks and since my early adolescence (I'm almost 24 now) there wasn't a day where I was not suffering from terrible lower back pain. Because of quarantine and full time home office since march, my condition got even worse. I was taking super strong medicine for a month and had to stop it (because of how strong it was) and even with that, the pain wasn't fully gone. My boyfriend suggested these videos for me and today, only 20 days after I started the challenge, I feel COMPLETELY pain free. It's crazy, I took every possible medicine for over a decade and nothing compares to the benefits of these videos. Thanks, Adriene (and my love for recommending it! <3)!

Day 20 ‚úîÔ∏è Hi friends! I had to recently adjust my yoga schedule to mornings instead of nights accommodate my day, and I was legit bummed for missing my usually scheduled practice. But then I remembered that this kind of thinking has actually set me up for a lot of failures in the past, because instead of going for excellence, I was going for perfection. Just like how I learned from these videos that it's not about hitting the poses perfectly, but rather doing the most mindfully best you can, I realized that I have to unlearn this. Whenever I feel like I start doing things because I have to versus because I want to, it's so easy to lose interest and look for ways to sabotage myself since "the resistance" in our brains make it that much more difficult. There was this quote I read somewhere that: "giving up on your goal because you had a setback is like slashing the other three tires because you got a flat" really resonated with me. Adjust, but don't stop (heyyoo)! Haha, keep it going friends! üôè

Just a warning about heros it can mess the ligaments in your knees up because the knee is a hinge joint. Eventually by placing your knee in the hero position too often and too much can stretch the ligaments out and they'll never return to normal unlike your muscles. Having stretched ligaments will make your joints like jello and make it hard to walk. If possible please don't do hero pose instead do a variation with your feet under your butt :) Stay safe everyone!
